# feasibility harness: container-only build output (mounted repo) + demo artifacts
.docker-target/
feasibility/demo/**/bin/
feasibility/demo/**/obj/
# transient build log sink written by dev.sh / cargo-dotnet (the pipeline core)
feasibility/_lastbuild.log
# rustc internal-compiler-error dumps (common while chasing nightly drift)
rustc-ice-*.txt
# cargo_tests corpus: per-crate build artifacts. The corpus tracks ONLY Cargo.toml + src/;
# the .cargo/config.toml (generated per-machine by cargo-dotnet), Cargo.lock, and target/ are
# regenerated and MUST NOT be committed (machine-specific paths -> dirty trees / broken native).
cargo_tests/**/target/
# same for each crate's csharp/ consumer project's own MSBuild output (bin/obj were accidentally
# staged once via a broad `git add .` on a new probe crate -- no other cargo_tests crate tracks
# these either, so make the exclusion explicit instead of relying on care alone).
cargo_tests/**/csharp/bin/
cargo_tests/**/csharp/obj/
cargo_tests/**/basecs/bin/
cargo_tests/**/basecs/obj/
# application examples are exercised in place; never commit their private-sysroot build output
examples/**/target/
# .NET runtime config emitted by cargo-dotnet / the linker into the run dir
.runtimeconfig.json
*.runtimeconfig.json
# macOS debug-symbol bundles from running compiled test binaries
*.dSYM/
# bench_rs_vs_cs benchmark artifacts (rebuildable, not source)
cargo_tests/bench_rs_vs_cs/binaries/
